Italy’s Berlusconi Supports France’s Lagarde as Next IMF Chief

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-05-19T18:39:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/italy-s-berlusconi-supports-france-s-lagarde-as-next-imf-chief.html
 Italian Prime Minister  Silvio Berlusconi  said French Finance Minister  Christine Lagarde  would
be “an excellent choice” as  Europe ’s candidate to replace
 Dominique Strauss-Kahn  as managing director of the  International
Monetary Fund , the Italian government said in an e-mailed
statement today. Berlusconi said it’s “fundamental” that
Europe should reach a common position on who the candidate
should be as soon as possible, the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 